40
00:02:28,819 --> 00:02:32,980
People have been asked in studies questions like, what are the odds that you’ll get

41
00:02:32,980 --> 00:02:36,560
a big promotion at work someday, what are the odds that you’ll ever get sacked from

42
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:40,340
work, and what are the chances that you’ll have a happy marriage, and what are the chances

43
00:02:40,340 --> 00:02:43,209
you’ll get a divorce, and so on, over and over.

44
00:02:43,209 --> 00:02:47,599
And people say compared to others, the chances are more good things will happen to me and

45
00:02:47,599 --> 00:02:49,439
fewer bad things will happen to me.

46
00:02:49,439 --> 00:02:55,230
Again, we don’t know which people are distorting, but we know people in general - the average

47
00:02:55,230 --> 00:02:59,420
